# pr-pipeline-gate

Pre-merge gate for {{PROJECT_NAME}} MRs/PRs targeting **`{{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}`**.
Runs read-only checks through {{MR_ADAPTER}} and reports readiness. It never
merges — merging follows the autonomy matrix in
`.agentic/guides/policy/ai-policy.md`.

## Triggers

- `/pr-pipeline-gate [MR/PR number]`
- Proactively after creating or updating an MR/PR, and before merge.
- "is the PR ready", "can we merge".

## Input contract

| Field | Required | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| MR/PR number | no | Defaults to the current branch's open MR/PR |

## Merge readiness checklist

| Check | Block merge if |
| --- | --- |
| Conflicts | not mergeable cleanly into `{{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}` |
| Sync | branch is behind the tip of `{{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}` |
| CI | any required check is failed, pending, or missing |
| Review | required approvals / review gates not satisfied per repo settings |

Informational-only signals (preview deploys, optional checks) are reported but
never block.

## Workflow

1. Fetch the integration branch (`git fetch origin {{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}`).
2. Query MR/PR state, mergeability, and check runs via {{MR_ADAPTER}}.
3. For each failed required check, capture the failing job name and, where cheap, the first error line from its log — a gate that says "CI red" without saying *where* wastes a round-trip.
4. Report the structured verdict below. If checks are still pending, say so under `## Blocking` with the re-run instruction — pending is not green.

## Policy references

- `.agentic/guides/policy/ai-policy.md` — merge/push autonomy per mode
- `.agentic/guides/policy/escalation-policy.md` — human-gated commands

## Output contract

End every response with exactly these five sections, in this order. They are
parsed fail-closed by `.claude/hooks/subagent_gate.py` — a missing section is
treated as Blocking. Use `None` when a section is empty.

## Summary

First line, exactly one of:
`PASS — MR/PR #N ready to merge to {{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}.`
`FAIL — MR/PR #N blocked (J blockers).`
Follow with the checks table: sync | mergeable | CI per required job.

## Why

One to three bullets: the decisive evidence (which checks, which commit SHA was verified — always verify the branch HEAD, not a superseded commit).

## Blocking

`None` if empty. Otherwise each blocker with its fix command, one per line.

## Non-blocking

`None` if empty. Otherwise informational signals (pending optional checks, preview deploy state).

## Escalate to human

`None` if empty. Otherwise: adapter credentials unavailable, or branch
protection requires checks this gate cannot see.
